  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Despite improvements in treatment, a significant part of patients have severe pain following
      knee arthroplasty. Preoperative identification of high-risk patients would allow for an
      intensive individualized analgesic treatment pre- and postoperatively and thus potentially in
      reduced pain acute and chronically.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
